:3,"key":"done","colorName":"green","name":"Done"}},"priority":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/priority/3","iconUrl":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/images/icons/priorities/major.svg","name":"Major","id":"3"},"issuetype":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/issuetype/1","id":"1","description":"A problem which impairs or prevents the functions of the product.","iconUrl":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=14803&avatarType=issuetype","name":"Bug","subtask":false,"avatarId":14803}}}}],"assignee":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=ssuehle","name":"ssuehle","key":"ssuehle","accountId":"557058:2d84875a-5ff3-4a22-b212-09d255ec5756","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/bce9c89090914545fe58159c4c1e5027?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FownerId%3Dssuehle%26avatarId%3D13702%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/bce9c89090914545fe58159c4c1e5027?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26ownerId%3Dssuehle%26avatarId%3D13702%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/bce9c89090914545fe58159c4c1e5027?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26ownerId%3Dssuehle%26avatarId%3D13702%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/bce9c89090914545fe58159c4c1e5027?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26ownerId%3Dssuehle%26avatarId%3D13702%26noRedirect%3Dtrue"},"displayName":"Scott Suehle","active":true,"timeZone":"America/New_York"},"updated":"2014-12-08T17:08:37.891-0600","status":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/status/6","description":"The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are closed can be reopened.","iconUrl":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/images/icons/statuses/generic.png","name":"Closed","id":"6","statusCategory":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/statuscategory/3","id":3,"key":"done","colorName":"green","name":"Done"}},"components":[{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/component/10204","id":"10204","name":"Admin Guide"}],"timeoriginalestimate":null,"customfield_13000":null,"description":"*Assessment*\r\n\r\nIn the [Eucalyptus Administration Guide, under the section 'Launch an Instance with a Role'|https://www.eucalyptus.com/docs/eucalyptus/4.0.1/index.html#admin-guide/roles_tasks_create_role_application.html], the steps are not correct.  As part of role creation, there is a two-step process (as mentioned in the [AWS documentation|http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/iam-roles-for-amazon-ec2.html#launch-instance-with-role-cli]).  It is as follows:\r\n\r\n# Create a trust policy to be used with creating the role (used with [euca-rolecreate|https://www.eucalyptus.com/docs/eucalyptus/4.0.1/index.html#euca2ools-guide/euare-rolecreate.html])\r\n# Create an access policy that grants permissions to the given resources (used with [euare-roleuploadpolicy|https://www.eucalyptus.com/docs/eucalyptus/4.0.1/index.html#euca2ools-guide/euare-roleuploadpolicy.html])\r\n\r\n\\\\\r\n\\\\\r\n----\r\n\\\\\r\n\\\\\r\n\r\nFor step 1, there are a couple of ways that it can be accomplished.  The first way is to use a trust policy file.  The steps are below:\r\n\r\n*Trust Policy File Method* \r\n\r\n# Create a trust policy file with the contents below and save it in a text file called 'role-trust-policy.json':\r\n{code}\r\n{\r\n  \"Version\": \"2012-10-17\",\r\n  \"Statement\": [\r\n    {\r\n      \"Effect\": \"Allow\",\r\n      \"Principal\": { \"Service\": \"ec2.amazonaws.com\"},\r\n      \"Action\": \"sts:AssumeRole\"\r\n    }\r\n  ]\r\n}\r\n{code}\r\n# Create the role using euare-rolecreate, specifying the trust policy file that was created:\r\n{code}\r\n# euare-rolecreate --role-name describe-instances -f role-trust-policy.json\r\n# euare-rolelistbypath \r\narn:aws:iam::408396244283:role/describe-instances\r\n{code}\r\n\r\n*Commandline Method*\r\n\r\nThe other way to create the role is to use the commandline options to specify the trust policy:  \r\n{code}\r\n# euare-rolecreate --role-name describe-instances --service http://compute.acme.eucalyptus-systems.com:8773/\r\n# euare-rolelistbypath \r\narn:aws:iam::408396244283:role/describe-instances\r\n{code}\r\n\\\\\r\n\\\\\r\n----\r\n\\\\\r\n\\\\\r\nStep 2 - this is where you add the access policy to the role.  The add an access policy, do the following:\r\n# Use the contents of step 1 from the Eucalyptus documentation - ['Launch an Instance with a Role'|https://www.eucalyptus.com/docs/eucalyptus/4.0.1/index.html#admin-guide/roles_tasks_create_role_application.html]\r\n# Apply the access policy to the role using [euare-roleuploadpolicy|https://www.eucalyptus.com/docs/eucalyptus/4.0.1/index.html#euca2ools-guide/euare-roleuploadpolicy.html]:\r\n{code}\r\n# euare-roleuploadpolicy --role-name mytestrole --policy-name s3-list-bucket --policy-document my-test-policy.json\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nThis change - along with the changes mentioned in DOC-1457 - need to be completed.","customfield_13200":null,"customfield_11300":null,"customfield_11500":null,"timetracking":{},"customfield_10401":null,"customfield_10005":null,"customfield_10600":null,"customfield_12900":null,"aggregatetimeestimate":null,"attachment":[],"summary":"Missing Complete Steps for Launching an Instance with a Role ","creator":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=hspencer","name":"hspencer","key":"hspencer","accountId":"557058:4a3a93bc-21f8-4658-9f5b-9cb484c910a7","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/ea43d7b9d5b27468a749f9bd25650176?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FownerId%3Dhspencer%26avatarId%3D10407%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/ea43d7b9d5b27468a749